@page "/"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<PageTitle>ScamAlert — protect the people you love</PageTitle>

<div class="row g-4 align-items-center mb-5">
    <div class="col-lg-7">
        <h1 class="display-6 fw-semibold mb-3">When you cannot be at the keyboard, someone still needs to be protected.</h1>
        <p class="lead text-secondary">
            ScamAlert watches remote-access attempts on the PCs that matter to your family—so refund scams, fake “tech support,”
            and surprise RDP sessions do not land silently while you are away.
        </p>
        <p class="text-secondary">
            If something tries to reach a loved one’s machine, your trusted contacts get alerted with a clear path to confirm
            or shut it down before a criminal walks them through a gift-card refund or account takeover.
        </p>
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg mt-2" href="/signup">Start protecting my family</a>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-5">
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body p-4">
                <h2 class="h5">What you get</h2>
                <ul class="mb-0 text-secondary">
                    <li class="mb-2">Alerts when inbound RDP, SSH, or Telnet looks suspicious.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">SMS escalation to people <em>you</em> trust—not a call center.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Peace of mind when parents or kids are online without you in the room.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
